{
  "texts": [
    "That is, we work under the assumption that no additional resources (either specific measurement models or calibration/training data) are available to power the detection methods.",
    "Offthe-shelf detectors include pre-trained classifiers, measurement model-agnostic metric-based classifiers with threshold values supplied by the developer, and commercially available detectors.",
    "Here, we consider four off-the-shelf detectors.",
    "Binoculars is implemented with the author-suggested decision threshold, foot_8 rather than calibrating on indistribution data as in the previous section.",
    "We consider two PLM detectors: OpenAI's detector and the ChatGPT detector; both use RoBERTa finetuned for AIGT classification using external GPTfamily datasets."
  ]
}